properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 23 at 8:27PM CST until January 24 at 6:00PM CST by NWS Kansas City/Pleasant HIll MO
properties.description:
...Winter Weather Returns Today...

.A strong storm system will bring light to moderate snow from
eastern Kansas through central Missouri this evening through the
overnight. Snow will exit the area from west to east through the
day tomorrow. Overall snow totals will be 1 to 2 inches over
eastern Kansas and western Missouri with central Missouri seeing
closer to 3 to as much as 6 inches.

* WHAT...Snow. Snow accumulations of 4 to 6 inches.

* WHERE...Carroll and Lafayette Counties.

* WHEN...Until 6 PM CST Friday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM CST FRIDAY
